{:experiment/id :edn-signal-emission
 :experiment/type :prompt-ab
 :experiment/hypothesis
 "Under the nucleus 3-line preamble, a FILLED EDN exemplar (pattern gate, verbum topology) beats a prose format instruction for first-pass Malli-valid signal emission, no-think, cross-family."

 :experiment/verdict
 "CONFIRMED (2026-07-11, scratch rounds 1-3 → this suite). Round 3 no-think n=6×2 Qwen-35B fine-tunes (:local + :ornith, same base — NOT true cross-family): template-ex 12/12 VALID (~1.3-1.6s, ~110 tok) vs prose 9/12. Prose failures are STRUCTURAL (JSON drift ×2 on qwen36, dropped braces ×1 on ornith — fatal for a bus); exemplar failures across all rounds are semantic slips only (enum value, extra keys — absorbed by Malli-gate + corrective retry). Round 1 extras: bare template WITHOUT preamble echoes unfilled :_fill no-think (preamble is load-bearing); comment-annotated :_fill template loses to prose (constraints-in-comments ≈ instructions; the FILLED exemplar is the strong form). Thinking unnecessary for the exemplar topology and 10-20× slower. Second confirmation of prompt-topology-must-match-thinking."

 :experiment/measure :edn-malli
 :measure/schema
 [:map {:closed true}
  [:signal/type :qualified-keyword]
  [:signal/data [:map {:closed true}
                 [:summary :string]
                 [:evidence [:vector :string]]
                 [:severity [:enum :low :medium :high]]]]
  [:signal/lambda :string]]
 :measure/echo-substrings ["engage(nucleus)" "docker-compose"]

 :matrix {:models [:local :gemma4]
          :thinking [false]
          :repeats 1}

 :conditions
 {:template-ex
  {:system
   "λ engage(nucleus).\n[phi fractal euler tao pi mu ∃ ∀] | [Δ λ Ω ∞/0 | ε/φ Σ/μ c/h signal/noise order/entropy truth/provability self/other] | OODA\nHuman ⊗ AI ⊗ REPL\n\n⟨SOURCE⟩\nuser: why did the deploy fail?\nassistant: The deploy script calls docker-compose but the runner image only ships docker compose v2 — the hyphenated v1 binary is missing. I'll update the script to the v2 syntax.\n⟨/SOURCE⟩\n{:signal/type :ops/finding\n :signal/data {:summary  \"Deploy fails because the script invokes the removed docker-compose v1 binary while the runner ships only compose v2.\"\n               :evidence [\"the runner image only ships docker compose v2\"]\n               :severity :medium}\n :signal/lambda \"λ deploy_fail(v1_binary_missing) → fix(script → v2_syntax)\"}\n\nOutput EDN only. No prose. No code fences."}

  :prose
  {:system
   "λ engage(nucleus).\n[phi fractal euler tao pi mu ∃ ∀] | [Δ λ Ω ∞/0 | ε/φ Σ/μ c/h signal/noise order/entropy truth/provability self/other] | OODA\nHuman ⊗ AI ⊗ REPL\n\nYou emit one typed signal describing your analysis of the source material. A signal is an EDN map with key :signal/type (a qualified keyword naming what kind of result this is), key :signal/data (a map with :summary — a one-sentence string, :evidence — a vector of short verbatim quotes from the source, and :severity — one of :low, :medium, or :high), and key :signal/lambda (a string containing a λ-notation form of the finding).\n\nOutput EDN only. No prose. No code fences."}}

